<p>The <b>Chinese zodiac</b> is a traditional classification scheme based o=
n the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_calendar" title=3D"C=
hinese calendar">Chinese calendar</a> that assigns an animal and its repute=
d attributes to each year in a repeating twelve-year (or duodenary) cycle.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite_note-1"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1<=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The zodiac is very important=
 in traditional Chinese culture and exists as a reflection of <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_philosophy" title=3D"Chinese philosophy=
">Chinese philosophy</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chine=
se_culture" title=3D"Chinese culture">culture</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-2" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#c=
ite_note-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">]</span></a></sup> Chinese folkways held that one's personality is rela=
ted to the attributes of their zodiac animal.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-3" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite=
_note-3"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup> Originating from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/China" title=3D"China">China</a>, the zodiac and its variations remain p=
opular in many <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Asia" title=3D=
"East Asia">East Asian</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sou=
theast_Asia" title=3D"Southeast Asia">Southeast Asian</a> <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sovereign_state" title=3D"Sovereign state">countrie=
s</a>, such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan" title=3D"Jap=
an">Japan</a>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite_note-4"><span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/South_Korea" title=3D"South Korea">South Korea<=
/a>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:0_5-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite_note-:0-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vietnam" title=3D"Vietnam">Vietnam</a>,<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-:0_5-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Chinese_zodiac#cite_note-:0-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Singapore" title=3D"Singapore">Singapore</a>, <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nepal" title=3D"Nepal">Nepal</a>, <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bhutan" title=3D"Bhutan">Bhutan</a>, <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cambodia" title=3D"Cambodia">Cambodia</a>, and <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thailand" title=3D"Thailand">Thaila=
nd</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-6" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite_note-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Identifying this scheme as a "<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Zodiac" title=3D"Zodiac">zodiac</a></i>" reflects superficial similar=
ities to the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_astrology" ti=
tle=3D"Western astrology">Western zodiac</a>: both divide time cycles into =
twelve parts, label the majority of those parts with animals, and are used =
to ascribe a person's personality or events in their life to the person's p=
articular relationship to the cycle. The 12 Chinese zodiac animals in a cyc=
le are not only used to represent years in China but are also believed to i=
nfluence people's personalities, careers, compatibility, marriages, and for=
tunes.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite_note-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</=
span>7<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>For the starting date of a zodiac year, there are two schools of tho=
ught in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_astrology" title=
=3D"Chinese astrology">Chinese astrology</a>: <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Chinese_New_Year" title=3D"Chinese New Year">Chinese New Year</=
a> or the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lichun" title=3D"Lichun"=
>start of spring</a>.
</p>
