<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_astrology" title=3D"=
Chinese astrology">Chinese astrology</a> the animal signs assigned by <b>ye=
ar</b> represent self-presentation or perception by others.<sup class=3D"no=
print Inline-Template Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wi=
kipedia:Citation needed"><span title=3D"This claim needs references to reli=
able sources. (July 2024)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup> It is a co=
mmon misconception that the animals assigned by year are the only signs, an=
d many <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_culture" title=3D"W=
estern culture">Western</a> descriptions of Chinese astrology only referenc=
e this system. There are also animal signs assigned by <b>month</b> (called=
 "inner animals"), by <b>day</b> (called "true animals"), and <b>hours</b> =
(called "secret animals"). The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ear=
th_(Wu_Xing)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Earth (Wu Xing)">Earth</a> is =
all twelve signs, with five seasons.<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Template T=
emplate-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed=
"><span title=3D"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (July 202=
4)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>
</p><p><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michel_Ferlus" title=3D"Mic=
hel Ferlus">Michel Ferlus</a> (2013) notes that the Old Chinese names of th=
e earthly branches are of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austroas=
iatic_languages" title=3D"Austroasiatic languages">Austroasiatic</a> origin=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Ferlus2013_13-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite_note-Ferlus2013-13"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 Some of Ferlus's comparisons are given below, with Old Chinese reconstruct=
ions cited from Baxter &amp; Sagart (2014).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-14" class=3D=
"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite_no=
te-14"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<ul><li><a href=3D"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E4%B8%91" class=3D"extiw=
" title=3D"wikt:=E4=B8=91">=E4=B8=91</a>: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Old_Chinese" title=3D"Old Chinese">Old Chinese</a> *[n=CC=A5]ru=CA=
=94 (compare Proto-<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vietic_language=
s" title=3D"Vietic languages">Viet-Muong</a> *c.lu=CB=90 '<a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Water_buffalo" title=3D"Water buffalo">water buffal=
o</a>')</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E5%8D%88" class=3D"extiw" ti=
tle=3D"wikt:=E5=8D=88">=E5=8D=88</a>: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Old_Chinese" title=3D"Old Chinese">Old Chinese</a> *[m].q=CA=B0=CB=A4a=
=CA=94 (compare Proto-<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vietic_langu=
ages" title=3D"Vietic languages">Viet-Muong</a> *m.=C5=8B=C9=99=CB=90=CB=80=
)</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E4%BA%A5" class=3D"extiw" ti=
tle=3D"wikt:=E4=BA=A5">=E4=BA=A5</a>: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Old_Chinese" title=3D"Old Chinese">Old Chinese</a> *[g]=CB=A4=C9=99=CA=
=94 (compare Northern Proto-<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vietic=
_languages" title=3D"Vietic languages">Viet-Muong</a> *ku=CB=90r=CB=80)</li=
></ul>
<p>There is also a lexical correspondence with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Austronesian_languages" title=3D"Austronesian languages">Austr=
onesian</a>:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Ferlus2013_13-1" class=3D"reference"><a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite_note-Ferlus2013-13">=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup>
</p>
<ul><li><a href=3D"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E6%9C%AA" class=3D"extiw=
" title=3D"wikt:=E6=9C=AA">=E6=9C=AA</a>: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Old_Chinese" title=3D"Old Chinese">Old Chinese</a> *m[=C9=99]t-s (c=
ompare <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atayal_language" title=3D"A=
tayal language">Atayal</a> mi=CB=90ts)</li></ul>
<p>The terms for the earthly branches are attested from <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shang_dynasty" title=3D"Shang dynasty">Shang dynasty<=
/a> inscriptions and were likely also used before Shang times. Ferlus (2013=
) suggests that the terms were ancient pre-Shang borrowings from Austroasia=
tic languages spoken in the Yangtze River region.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Ferlus=
2013_13-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chi=
nese_zodiac#cite_note-Ferlus2013-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>1=
