<p>Within the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Four_Pillars_of_Dest=
iny" title=3D"Four Pillars of Destiny">Four Pillars</a>, the year is the pi=
llar representing information about the person's family background and soci=
ety or relationship with their grandparents.<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Te=
mplate Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citatio=
n needed"><span title=3D"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (=
July 2024)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup> The person's age can also=
 be easily deduced from their sign, the current sign of the year, and the p=
erson's generational disposition (teens, mid-20s, and so on). For example, =
a person born a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tiger_(zodiac)" ti=
tle=3D"Tiger (zodiac)">Tiger</a> is 12, 24, 36, (etc.) years old in the yea=
r of the Tiger (2022); in the year of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Rabbit_(zodiac)" title=3D"Rabbit (zodiac)">Rabbit</a> (2023), that =
person is one year older.
</p><p>The following table shows the 60-year cycle matched up to the <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gregorian_calendar" title=3D"Gregorian c=
alendar">Gregorian calendar</a> for 1924=E2=80=932043. The <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexagenary_cycle" title=3D"Sexagenary cycle">sexag=
enary cycle</a> begins at <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lichun" =
title=3D"Lichun">lichun</a> about February 4 according to some <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Astrological_sign" title=3D"Astrological sign"=
>astrological</a> sources.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-15" class=3D"reference"><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite_note-15"><span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>15<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
><sup id=3D"cite_ref-16" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite_note-16"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</spa=
n>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
