<p>As the Chinese zodiac is derived according to the ancient <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wuxing_(Chinese_philosophy)" title=3D"Wuxing (Ch=
inese philosophy)">Five Elements Theory</a>, every <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_language" title=3D"Chinese language">Chinese</a> s=
ign is associated with five elements with relations, among those elements, =
of interpolation, interaction, over-action, and counter-action=E2=80=94beli=
eved to be the common law of motions and changes of creatures in the <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Universe" title=3D"Universe">universe</a=
>. Different people born under each animal sign supposedly have different p=
ersonalities, and practitioners of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Chinese_astrology" title=3D"Chinese astrology">Chinese astrology</a> consu=
lt such <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_culture" title=3D"=
Chinese culture">traditional</a> details and compatibilities to offer putat=
ive guidance in life or for love and marriage.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-17" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite=
_note-17"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup> A common way to explore zodiac compatibility is with =
a chart showing how each zodiac sign interacts other signs. For example, co=
nstellations that are considered compatible with each other may have simila=
r values and interests, while incompatible constellations may have conflict=
ing personalities and ways of communicating.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-18" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chinese_zodiac#cite=
_note-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>18<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
