<li>The term <a href=3D"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E9%9B%9E" class=3D"=
extiw" title=3D"wikt:=E9=9B=9E">=E9=9B=9E</a> <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Rooster_(zodiac)" title=3D"Rooster (zodiac)">Rooster</a> can be=
 translated interchangeably with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C=
hicken" title=3D"Chicken">Chicken</a>, as well as the female <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hen_(chicken)" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"He=
n (chicken)">Hen</a>. However, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roo=
ster_(zodiac)" title=3D"Rooster (zodiac)">Rooster</a> is the most commonly =
used one among all the synonyms in English-speaking countries.<sup class=3D=
"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><=
